---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Leaderboard" description="LLM code generation pass rates across languages — Tyra benchmark results">
  <style>
    .lb-header {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .lb-header p {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      max-width: 680px;
    }

    .highlight-row td {
      background: rgba(247, 129, 102, 0.07);
    }

    .highlight-row td:first-child {
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .detail-card {
      background: var(--bg-secondary);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .detail-card h3 {
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .stat-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 1rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .stat-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }

    .stat-box {
      background: var(--bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .stat-value {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .stat-label {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin-top: 0.25rem;
    }

    .caveat-list {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .caveat-list li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .methodology-note {
      background: var(--bg-secondary);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--border);
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="lb-header">
    <h1>Leaderboard</h1>
    <p>
      LLM code generation pass rates across languages. 100 tasks, generated by Claude,
      evaluated by automated test harness. Tyra results use multi-seed methodology;
      other languages are single-seed estimates.
    </p>
  </div>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Language</th>
        <th>Pass rate</th>
        <th>Method</th>
        <th>Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Ruby</td>
        <td>99.0%</td>
        <td>Single seed</td>
        <td>Massive training data</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Crystal</td>
        <td>96.0%</td>
        <td>Single seed</td>
        <td>Ruby-like syntax, strong type system</td>
      </tr>
      <tr class="highlight-row">
        <td>Tyra + spec</td>
        <td>88.7%</td>
        <td>Multi-seed mean (3 seeds)</td>
        <td>Zero training data; spec injected as system prompt</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Go</td>
        <td>81.0%</td>
        <td>Single seed</td>
        <td>Verbosity leads to more surface area for errors</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>V</td>
        <td>49.0%</td>
        <td>Single seed</td>
        <td>Systems language, limited training data</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Gleam</td>
        <td>37.0%</td>
        <td>Single seed</td>
        <td>Test harness wrapping overhead; functional/Erlang ecosystem</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="detail-card">
    <h3>Tyra detail — v0.11.0, run56</h3>
    <div class="stat-grid">
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">88.7%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Mean pass rate (3 seeds)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">98%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Any-seed (at least 1 of 3 passes)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">77%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">All-seed (all 3 seeds pass)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0;">
      Model: Claude. Tasks: 100 problems from the static corpus. Spec injected as system prompt.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Methodology</h2>

  <div class="methodology-note">
    <strong>Multi-seed vs single-seed:</strong> Tyra results use 3 random seeds and report the mean,
    which is more robust than a single point estimate. Single-seed figures for other languages are
    estimates based on one run and may have higher variance. A same-condition multi-seed comparison
    across all languages is planned for a future benchmark run.
  </div>

  <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">
    The benchmark generates code from the language specification (or standard documentation for
    established languages), runs the test suite without human intervention, and records pass/fail.
    No human review or debugging of generated code.
  </p>

  <h2>Caveats</h2>

  <ul class="caveat-list">
    <li>Tyra requires spec injection; other languages do not. This is an intentional part of Tyra's design, not a handicap for other languages.</li>
    <li>Single-seed figures for non-Tyra languages are point estimates from a single run. They may vary across seeds.</li>
    <li>Gleam's 37% reflects the test harness wrapping overhead for Erlang/OTP projects — not purely the language's LLM-generability.</li>
    <li>Ruby's 99% reflects extensive training data, not language design properties.</li>
    <li>Task selection and difficulty affect all figures. The corpus targets "typical web backend / CLI" tasks.</li>
    <li>Tyra v0.11.0 results; the compiler is in active development and results may improve.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Reproduce</h2>

  <p style="color: var(--text-muted);">
    The benchmark harness and corpus are in the Tyra repository.
    See <a href="https://github.com/tyra-lang/tyra/tree/main/bench" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/tyra-lang/tyra/tree/main/bench</a>
    for reproduction instructions.
  </p>
</Base>
